# ALIS public mirror policy:
# - code, docs, and build/release scripts are public by default
# - secrets, licensed assets, generated outputs, and local machine state are never public
# - if a future workflow needs secrets, keep them outside the repository and outside the mirror

# Workspace and local machine state
.claude/**
.vs/**
.vscode/**
langchain_env/**
LocalAppData/**
tmp/**
tmpclaude-*
.env
.ignore
.clinerules
.vsconfig
agent_policy.yaml
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
CODEX.md
*.code-workspace
*.code-workspace.backup

# Generated artifacts and local outputs
Binaries/**
Build/**
DerivedDataCache/**
Intermediate/**
Saved/**
Releases/**
artifacts/**
scripts/ue/check/reports/**

# Game content and packaged assets
# Public mirror excludes UE asset payloads and packaged binaries.
# This keeps the mirror compatible with open-source code flow while avoiding redistribution of licensed content.
**/*.uasset
**/*.umap
**/*.ubulk
**/*.uexp
**/*.utoc
**/*.ucas
**/*.pak
Content/**
Config/**
Plugins/**/Binaries/**
Plugins/**/Content/**
Plugins/**/Intermediate/**
Plugins/**/Resources/**
Plugins/**/Data/**
Plugins/InstanceArrayTool/**
Plugins/Local/**
Plugins/ThirdParty/**
Plugins/**/ThirdParty/**
Test/**
tools/**
Wiki/**

# Internal docs and local automation
# These are excluded because they are repo-local workflow helpers or internal machine setup,
# not because ALIS documentation is private by default.
docs/agents/**
docs/ci/**
docs/debugging/**
docs/integration/**
docs/loading/**
scripts/config/**
scripts/ci/**
scripts/git/hooks/**
scripts/utils/**
scripts/scripts_list.txt

# Internal project files
Alis_sanitized.uproject
nul
